CAPE TOWN - Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa on Friday urged the National Education, Health and Allied Workers’ Union (Nehawu) to take action against those who steal from the state. Ramaphosa was speaking at the union's 30th anniversary celebrations in Cape Town. READ: Deputy Presidency warns against phishing emails in Ramaphosa's name He says state capture has impacted South Africa in a negative way by giving the country bad publicity around the globe. "Our state is being captured by people who have no interest in our people, they want to rob money that belongs to the people,” Ramaphosa said. “Our state is talked about in the most negative way in the world, captured by certain families." eNCA